                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d493">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">560.AL/8–247: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Consulate at Geneva</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-08-02T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 2, 1947—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>943. For Clayton from Wood. Steelman said at 2:00 p.m. EST: “Send secret word to
                    Clayton that President gives him authority if he needs to use it and will
                    approve <gloss target="#t_TAC1">TAC</gloss> letter<note n="1" xml:id="d493fn1"
                        >Telegram 951 to Geneva, August 5, informed Clayton that the words <gloss
                            target="#t_TAC1">TAC</gloss> letter should have read “<gloss
                            target="#t_TAC1">TAC</gloss> recommendation as amended by Secretary’s
                        letter.” (560.AL/8–247) This meant that he had the authority to cut the
                        tariff on wool.</note> Monday.” Understands approval will not be made
                    public. Also said: “The Boss and I know what Will is up against and hope he has
                    luck”. [Wood.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
